-- Common Amass Commands --

1. Basic Usage: This command discovers subdomains for the specified target domain.

amass enum -d <target_domain>


2. File Input: This command reads a list of domains from a file and discovers subdomains for each one.

amass enum -df <file>


3. Output to File: This command saves the discovered subdomains in a specified output file. This gives the Amass tool the ability for post-test analysis.

amass enum -d <target_domain> -o <output_file>


4. Brute Force Subdomain Enumeration: Use brute forcing to discover subdomains with a wordlist.

amass enum -d <target_domain> -brute -w <wordlist>


5. DNS Resolution: Resolve discovered subdomains to their respective IP addresses.

amass resolve -d <target_domain>


